An Act requiring the department of the state auditor to certify compliance as a prerequisite for
additional compensation for a member of the General Court.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 2. Chapter 3 of the General Laws, as appearing in 2022 Official Edition, is
2 hereby amended by inserting after section 9D the following section:- “No member of the general
3 court shall be eligible for any additional compensation that a member may receive pursuant to
4 section 9B, nor an allowance for expenses pursuant to section 9C without certification from the
5 department of the state auditor that the member is in compliance with all requests made by the
6 department of the state auditor pursuant to section 12 of chapter 11 of the General Laws.”
